ما هو stc tv؟

stc tv، خدمة بث ترفيهية توفر لك أفضل الأفلام، والمسلسلات، والأفلام الوثائقية، وبرامج الأطفال وأكثر من خلال مجموعة من أفضل الشركاء المحليين والعالميين. كما يمكنك الاستمتاع بمشاهدة مجموعة كبيرة من الأعمال الحصرية والأصلية، بالإضافة لعدد كبير من أفضل القنوات التلفزيونية المباشرة المحلية والعالمية بما فيها المفتوحة والمشفرة. كل هذا مصمّم حسب رغباتك في مكان وحساب واحد، لتتمكن من البحث في المحتوى الترفيهي بسهولة وإنشاء قائمة مشاهدة واحدة تضم جميع اختياراتك المفضّلة.

Make sure the mobile device you are using to cast is on the same Wi-Fi network as your Chromecast or TV with Chromecast built-in.
  • Open stc tv app.
  • Tap the Cast button   on the top right corner of any screen.
  • Now select the device you'd like to cast to.
  • When you're connected, the Cast button will change color , letting you know you're connected.
  • Now play any movie or episode on the app and watch it on the bigger screen.

To stop casting, tap the Cast button and then tap Disconnect.

Is Cast to TV feature available on my subscription plan?

Please sign into stctv.com and check your subscription details on My Account section to know your subscription plan. If your plan is Lite, then you will not have access to Cast to TV feature.

Downloads on stc tv mobile app

Downloading content for offline viewing is available on stc tv iOS and Android mobile app. You can download your favorite movies and TV shows and watch them later, even without access to Internet. To identify what is downloadable, just look for the Download button next to the video.

Which content can I download?

There are hundreds of videos available for download on stc tv.

To download:

  1. Select the movie or show you’d like to download.
  2. Movies that are available for download have a download button in the details page. In case of series, the download button can be seen after tapping the expand icon next to the episode.
  3. Tap Download to begin the download.
  4. Once your download is complete, go to Downloads section from the menu and start watching.

* Please note that download availability varies from title to title. If the download button is not available on the details page, it means the content cannot be downloaded due to contractual agreement with the content partner.

On which devices can I download content on mobile app?

On which devices can I download content on mobile app?

Downloads feature is supported on all iOS mobile and tablet devices with iOS 11.3 or later. Similarly, mobile and tablet Android devices of OS 5 and up are supported.

How long do my downloads remain stored in my device?

Once a title is downloaded, it will remain in the Downloads section of your device for the next 30 days. Please keep in mind that you can watch all the videos you’ve downloaded on that specific device, regardless of the Profile used to download.

Are there any download limits?

You can have up to 100 downloads in your account at a time. These limits are set at the account level, not per profile or device. You’ll have access to your downloads for 30 days, unless the episode or movie expires from stc tv before that. If a download expires before you’ve watched it, you may be able to renew it.

How to renew expired download?
If some of your downloaded videos have expired, you can just tap Renew download and then choose from options available.

Are downloaded content safe for family viewing?

Parental control level on the profile applies also to the downloaded videos. Yes, you can easily make downloaded content safe for family viewing by setting an appropriate parental control level on the profile and using profile lock.

How to delete downloads?

If you’ve reached the maximum number of downloads or run out of space, you can delete some of your downloads to make room for new ones.

To delete some downloads:

  • Go to Downloads from the menu.
  • Tap edit icon at the top of the screen.
  • Tap cross icon to remove the downloads you want to delete.

To delete all downloads:

• Go to Settings and then Downloads.
  • Tap Delete all downloads to delete all downloads at one go from your device.

Is Downloads/Offline viewing feature available on my subscription plan?

Please sign into stctv.com and subscription details on My Account section to know your subscription plan. If your plan is Lite, then you will not have access to Downloads/offline viewing feature.

How to create, edit or switch user profiles on stc tv?

How to create, edit or switch user profiles on stc tv?

User profiles provide more personalized viewing experience for you and rest of your family. If you share your stc tv account with your family or friends, then you may create separate profiles to keep track of Watchlist, resume watching program where you left off and channel favorites. You can also secure profiles with profile lock. Create up to 5 profiles for one account.

Creating Profiles

The primary profile for your account is automatically created as default profile.

*Please note that default profile cannot be deleted. You cannot use ‘default’ as a profile name for any of other profiles.

stctv.com

  1. Hover on the Profile icon (indicated by an alphabet) on the top-right left of the screen.
  2. Click Manage Profiles or Profile Settings.
  3. Click Add Profile to create a new profile.
  4. Add the following details to the new profile

• Profile Name – Enter a name.
  • Profile Lock preference – This option allows you to lock your profile. Every time you wish to access this profile or update preferences of this profile, you will be prompted to enter the account password.
  • Preferred Audio – Your audio language preference will be applied on the video settings if selected language is available
  • Preferred Subtitle - Your subtitle language preference will be applied on the video settings if selected language is available
  • Auto Play Next Episode – This option will automatically play the next episode of a series once you complete watching the current episode.
  • Parental Control Level – This option applies the selected parental control setting on this profile.

• Parental Control Level – This option applies the selected parental control setting on this profile.
  • You can slide the bar to select between parental control ratings: Family (F), PG, 15, 18, R18 (contains restricted content)

1. Click Save to update your profile settings.

If you have opted for Profile Lock, you will be prompted to enter account password to save the changes.

Mobile apps

  1. On ‘Who’s watching?’ screen, tap Add Profile. If you are on the app home screen, tap the burger icon on top-left corner of the home screen and tap on the profile icon (indicated by an alphabet). Then tap Add Profile on ‘Who’s watching? screen.
  2. Add the following details to the new profile

• Profile Name – Enter a name.
  • Profile Lock preference – This option allows you to lock your profile. Every time you wish to access this profile or update preferences of this profile, you will be prompted to enter the account password.
  • Preferred Audio – Your audio language preference will be applied on the video settings if selected language is available.
  • Preferred Subtitle - Your subtitle language preference will be applied on the video settings if selected language is available.
  • Auto Play Next Episode – This option will automatically play the next episode of a series once you complete watching the current episode.
  • Parental Control Level – This option applies the selected parental control setting on this profile.

• Parental Control Level – This option applies the selected parental control setting on this profile.
  • You can slide the bar to select between parental control ratings: Family (F), PG, 15, 18, R18 (contains restricted content).

1. Click Save/Done to update your profile settings.

If you have opted for Profile Lock, you will be prompted to enter account password to save the changes.

Editing or Deleting Profiles

stctv.com

  1. Hover on the Profile icon (indicated by an alphabet) on the top-left corner of the screen.
  2. Click Manage Profiles or Profile Settings.
  3. Click Edit on the profile you want to edit to update your profile settings.
  4. Enter account password if the selected profile is locked.
  5. Click Save to apply changes.

 On Edit Profile screen, click Delete Profile to delete the profile. Confirm deletion.

 Please note that the profile which is currently active cannot be deleted.

Mobile apps

Mobile apps

  3. Go to the profile you want to update, and tap Edit on the profile icon.
  4. Enter account password if the selected profile is locked.

stctv.com

  3. Enter account password if the selected profile is locked.

Mobile apps

1. Tap the burger icon on the top-left corner of the home screen.
  2. Tap the profile icon.

How to cast to Apple TV using Airplay casting feature?
To cast stc tv from an iOS mobile device to your Apple TV, first make sure that both the devices are on the same network.

• Tap the Airplay cast button   on the top-right corner of the stc tv screen.
  • Now select your Apple TV from Connect to a Device screen.

Once connected, play any movie or episode on the app and watch it on the bigger screen.

How can I change my registered email address?

In case you have mis-typed your email address while completing the registration process, you can provide us with the correct email address and we will correct it on your behalf upon your request. Please note that your registered mobile number will remain the same and no changes to your subscription will be made.

Can I get my subscription cancelled by contacting stc tv support team?

Can I get my subscription cancelled by contacting stc tv support team?

Unfortunately, our support team cannot cancel your subscription on your behalf. The only way possible is as shown in the FAQs under "How can I unsubscribe?". In case you are not able to find this information, our support team will be happy to take you through it.

Why am I getting an error with my credit card payment?

The credit card payment failure could happen for a variety of reasons that are determined by cardholder’s bank. Before entering your card details, please check:

•  If your card is active and hasn’t expired
  • If you have entered CVV correctly (code on the reverse on your card)
  •  If your card issuing bank allows your type of card to make online transactions.

If you are still facing issues with your card after checking the above points, then you may opt to enter another card details, or select another payment option. Please contact support@stctv.com or Live Chat with one of our representatives on our website if the issue persists.

I am facing “You have reached the maximum number of devices allowed on your account” error while trying to sign in. What should I do?
Your stc tv subscription comes with multiple device access depending on your subscription plan.

Mobile app - If you are trying to sign into mobile app and see this error on "My devices" screen, please delete one of the listed devices. As soon you delete a device, you will be automatically signed in.

Website: Please close the “maximum devices reached” error message and check "My Device" section. Delete a device by clicking the button next to the device, the page will automatically refresh after that and you will be automatically signed in.

Set-top box or Smart TV app – If you are trying to sign into TV application and see this error, please choose “Delete Device”. You will be directed to “My device” screen where you can delete any of the listed devices.

*Please note that you can delete a device after 30 days of use.

How to delete a registered device from my account?

To delete a device from your account from the web browser:

1. Sign into your account here.
  2. Go to Profile Settings and then My Devices.
  3. Click Manage and click the cross next to the device you want to delete.
  4. Click Save to apply your changes.

To delete a device from your account from an iOS and Android mobile app:

To delete a device from your account from an iOS and Android mobile app:

  1. Sign into your stc tv app on your mobile device.
  2. Go to More > My Account and My devices.

How to reset or update account password?

Resetting password on Web "stctv.com"

• On the sign-in screen, enter your login ID (phone or Email), then click "next".
  • Click Forgot Password.
  • Enter your phone or Email associated with the account. (For mobile subscribers, please enter your mobile number starting with the country code and without zeros).
  • You will receive a PIN Code on your mobile number or email address.
  • Enter the PIN Code on the screen to complete verification.
  • Set up a new password and click Continue to sign in with the new password.

Resetting password on mobile apps

Resetting password on mobile apps

  • On the sign-in screen, enter your login ID (phone or Email), then click "next".
  • On the sign-in screen, tap Reset Password.
  • You will receive a PIN Code on your email address or mobile number.
  • Enter the PIN Code on the mobile app screen and tap Confirm to sign in.
  • You will receive an email or SMS notification with the new password. Please keep in mind to use the new password for the subsequent sign-ins or assign your own password by following these steps:
    • Tap More on bottom right of the screen
    • Now go to My Account
    • Tap Change Password
    • Enter current password
    • Choose a new password and enter it again to confirm
    • Tap Save Changes to update the password

Customers who are subscribed to stc tv Home through Landline Number and would like to reset their PIN; Please contact stc Customer Care on 900 to assist you.

What happens when my subscription payment through credit card is not successful?
In the event that a transaction error has occurred while processing your credit card payment, a refund in most cases will be issued to the same credit card you used for the original purchase.
